Package: tranSurv
Title: Transformation Model Based Estimation of Survival and Regression
        Under Dependent Truncation and Independent Censoring
Version: 1.2.2
Authors@R: c(person("Sy Han (Steven)", "Chiou", email =
        "schiou@utdallas.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Jing",
        "Qian", email = "qian@schoolph.umass.edu", role = "aut"))
Description: A latent, quasi-independent truncation time is assumed to
        be linked with the observed dependent truncation time, the
        event time, and an unknown transformation parameter via a
        structural transformation model. The transformation parameter
        is chosen to minimize the conditional Kendall's tau (Martin and
        Betensky, 2005) <doi:10.1198/016214504000001538> or the
        regression coefficient estimates (Jones and Crowley, 1992)
        <doi:10.2307/2336782>. The marginal distribution for the
        truncation time and the event time are completely left
        unspecified. The methodology is applied to survival curve
        estimation and regression analysis.
